snippet.textDisplay:
Beautifully sung.. I remember my dado listening to this song in Naseem Begum's voice.. Beautiful resurrection.. 

I don't think it should matter if ur Pakistani, Indian, Kashmiri, British etc etc.. This was a song for then and now it's being played for the remembrance of the people who lost their lives.. War is always between 2 governments and politicians.. Not between the people who live in those countries.. I'm British/Pakistani and here in the UK, Pakistani and Indian live together.. Become friends.. Share happiness and sadness together.. Even Jewish people and Muslims are friends and also Indians and British.. All have had differences in the past and present but as long as both are respectful of each other's religions and beliefs nothing comes between them.. I lost alot of family during the Pakistan/Indian war but I don't resent any Indian for wot happened.. Be respectful and forgiving.. Ask the All Mighty for forgiveness and peace in the world.. Luv from London UK xxx
